üìò Security Concepts ‚Äì PG-DITISS (Aug 2025)
Session 10: Ethical Hacking, Reconnaissance, Scanning, Footprinting & Tools
üîπ BASIC MCQs (10)
1. Ethical hacking is performed to:
A. Damage systems
B. Identify and fix vulnerabilities
C. Steal information
D. Bypass laws

2. A security evaluation plan mainly defines:
A. Hardware cost
B. Scope and methodology of testing
C. Network speed
D. UI design

3. Ethical hacking must always begin with:
A. Exploitation
B. Permission and scope definition
C. Port scanning
D. Vulnerability scanning

4. Foot-printing is the process of:
A. Exploiting vulnerabilities
B. Gathering information about a target
C. Crashing servers
D. Writing reports

5. Social engineering attacks mainly exploit:
A. Network protocols
B. Human psychology
C. Encryption flaws
D. Hardware bugs

6. Traceroute is used to:
A. Scan ports
B. Identify network path to target
C. Exploit services
D. Capture packets

7. Port scanning is used to identify:
A. Open ports and services
B. Passwords
C. Encryption keys
D. Malware

8. Network scanning mainly focuses on:
A. Live hosts
B. Vulnerabilities
C. Passwords
D. Logs

9. Vulnerability scanning identifies:
A. Network topology
B. Security weaknesses
C. User behavior
D. Packet loss

10. SYN scan is also known as:
A. Full connect scan
B. Stealth scan
C. XMAS scan
D. Idle scan

üî∏ INTERMEDIATE MCQs (10)
11. Which ethical hacking type simulates real attacker behavior?
A. White-box testing
B. Black-box testing
C. Code review
D. Static analysis

12. Foot-printing includes collecting information like:
A. IP addresses and DNS details
B. Encryption keys
C. User passwords
D. System logs

13. Social engineering is dangerous because it:
A. Uses malware
B. Bypasses technical controls
C. Needs encryption
D. Is slow

14. Traceroute primarily uses which protocol?
A. TCP
B. UDP / ICMP
C. FTP
D. HTTP

15. SYN scan is stealthy because it:
A. Completes TCP handshake
B. Does not complete TCP handshake
C. Uses UDP
D. Uses ICMP

16. NULL scan sends packets with:
A. SYN flag
B. FIN flag
C. No flags set
D. All flags set

17. XMAS scan is named because packets have:
A. No flags
B. All flags set
C. Only SYN flag
D. Only ACK flag

18. IDLE scan hides attacker identity by using:
A. Proxy server
B. Zombie host
C. Firewall
D. VPN

19. Vulnerability scanning differs from port scanning because it:
A. Finds open ports
B. Identifies known weaknesses
C. Maps network
D. Captures packets

20. Reconnaissance using search engines is called:
A. Active recon
B. Passive recon
C. Exploitation
D. Privilege escalation

üî∫ ADVANCED MCQs (10) ‚Äì CCEE TRAP + LAB-FOCUSED
