B. Exploitation
C. Reconnaissance
D. Maintaining access

23. Passive footprinting reduces risk because it:
A. Uses malware
B. Does not directly interact with target
C. Uses exploits
D. Uses scanning tools

24. FIN scan attempts to bypass firewalls by:
A. Sending malformed packets
B. Sending FIN packets only
C. Flooding traffic
D. Using SYN flood

25. Why XMAS/NULL/FIN scans may evade detection?
A. Use encryption
B. Do not follow standard TCP behavior
C. Use UDP
D. Use ICMP

26. FOCA tool is mainly used for:
A. Port scanning
B. Metadata extraction and fingerprinting
C. Password cracking
D. Packet sniffing

27. Burp Suite spidering helps in:
A. Exploiting vulnerabilities
B. Mapping application attack surface
C. Capturing packets
D. Scanning network

28. Vulnerability scanning should be done:
A. Before footprinting
B. After exploitation
C. After port and network scanning
D. Only after reporting

29. TreePad tool is used for:
A. Exploitation
B. Reporting and documentation
C. Scanning
D. Packet capture

30. Session 10 mainly tests understanding of:
A. Programming logic
B. Reconnaissance and scanning methodologies
C. Hardware design
D. Database tuning

